m value and capture the greatest opportunity for all stakeholders strategic directionthe strategic direction of aramark is to lead further in developing its facilities uniform and career capabilities through key acquisitions they want to move and expand their facilities across the globe strategic infrastructure the strategic infrastructure of aramark is to focus on the people and customer system by focusing their business on the connection with the consumers they also have a core value of information system by wanting to have a competitive advantage in expanding and growing the sbus is that aramark has many difference services like food facility and uniform main dominate strategy customer intimacyaramark wants to have longterm value with their customers they want to build their products through their customers and they want to satisfy them aramark considers and addresses issues that matter most to clients customers employees and communitieslow cost and differentiationaramark address differentiation by engaging and supporting the valuables and assets competence commitment and creativity that appeal to each individual customers armarak focuses on low cost by having bulk supply for industries like colleges and prisons to appeal to a variety of customers aramarks ecommercearamark uses an ecommerce portal that engages the community on campus this is done by providing a campus dining program that allows a onecard system this provides information like nutrition meal plans and eating options aramark also engages in twitter and facebook to keep in touch with customers and employers competitive advantage with aramarks ecommercearamark can sell items online which is convenient for customers and they can communicate to customers easier through social media allowing them to reach a broader customer base they are also technologically savvy which appeals to college students aramarks cloud computingaramark engages in cloud computing by listing any job openings to people on the web they also increase efficiency in bb transactions to suppliers with the cloud computing aramark can engage with businesses they supply to online so they can access the suppliers more efficient and effectively rivalry amoung existing firmssome rivalries among existing firms for aramark are compass groupsodexocintaspotential entrantsthe threat of potential entrants is on aramarks radar since they have a large global scope other companies can focus on a regional scope that can possibly steal some market share suppliersaramarks suppliers are national urban league diversity inc congresocatalystwomens food service forumupward synergy out and equal human rights compainintermediaries  buyerssome intermediaries and buyers include healthcare institutionsuniversities and schoolsgrocery storesstadiums and arenasfacilities managementexamples of companies includeamerican indian college panjdecongreso substitutesaramarks substitutes include  local vendorsregional supplierscatering companieslocal restaurants marketing information and research specific marketing research areas what kind of food does aramark want to focus on aramark could conduct a focus group to a portion of their consumers to see what food they like how much they would spend on that food and if they would rather have packed lunches or buy aramarks food  how to figure out where to start with location and consumers which of aramarks services are used mostsurveys could be used to find out which of aramarks services are used most this will allow the company to become the leader of that specific industry also aramark could use growth data to determine which industries are trending and put more time to perfect that industrymarketing information and research marketing research process selected areawhat kind of food should aramark focus on problem definitionsecondary research was conducted in order to figure out the problem of location and income for students and teachers the overweight issues and what food to serve is also aramarks attraction of research exploratory research desginaramark did a focus group with three difference teachers and six students to see how much they were willing to pay for food and what kind of food they were attracted to quantitative research designaramark provided a survey to their consumers to allow any feedback on the service of the company and about the types of food people enjoyed or did not like understanding consumer behaviorpsychological factor perceptionpsychological factor attitudesconsumers will form attitudes about nutrition quality and trendiness for the food they consumer aramarks food services must coincide with the consumers attitudes about the foodidea to positively influence consumer behavior aramark could create an advertisement in which a football game is being played and some fans are eating food in the stadium that is provided by aramark suppliers could learn about this company through classical conditioning in which every time they see a football game being played they think of aramark this could positively influence suppliers behavior of buying from aramarkcreating customer satisfaction and loyalty aramarks satisfaction and loyalty aramark creates satisfaction and loyalty by focusing their attention of the specific needs and wants of the customers aramark personally designs each product to the customers wants with this personal attention on their customers aramark builds trust with each customer aramarks customer satisfaction scores aramark won two awards related to their customer satisfaction such asgold uniform supplier award in food process magazine  readers choice hormel foods spirit of excellence awardthese awards correlates to aramarks high success rates with their customers and suppliers source wwwaramarkcom customer satisfaction and loyalty plan for aramark idea in order to improve satisfaction and loyalty aramark could have a rewards cardimplementation plan with this rewards card aramark customers will be able to get points when purchasing products with them after they get a certain amount of points the customers could get  off on the next order this will make loyal customers stay and be satisfied when receiving this discount segmentation targeting and positioningmajor target market segments  sports arenas entertainmentaramark has a  second spot titled sports it describes how being apart of something bigger than yourself is great their ending phrase great things happen when you put on a uniform creates a relationship between their service and sports teams educationaramark is a leading provider of dining facilities and conference center management to colleges across the country retail outletsaramark describes a large selection of products to customers with diverse needs also quality and accessibility is very important with aramarks retail outletsaramarks marketing variableswe would recommend aramark to use demographic segmentation this allows each product to be segments to either age workers vs college students gender male vs female or income different prices this will create a larger segmentation group for customers and will generate more revenue aramarks marketing strategy differentiated aramark provides services in nearly every industry therefore they market to several different segments with a marketing mix strategy matched specifically to their desires and expectations segmentation targeting and positioningpositioning maptarget market segment sports arenascompeting brands compass group sodexocintus corporationattributes used by buyers in the segment to understand brands qualityreputation pricenutrition taste cintasfundamental way to position the productflexibilities of serviceshigh qualitydiverse advertising for different productscustomer satisfactiondimensions to position aramarks brandscommunity service good will flexibility aramark could conduct secondary research on location income for students overweight issues and nutritional needs in order to pinpoint what the consumer needs 