nd loyalty this is clearly evidenced in aramarks insight to impact campaign in the sports and entertainment industry they communicate value and product uniqueness by being insightful striving to become recognized as worldclass in gathering data that predicts guest behaviors and stays ahead of partner needs which is also helping to build a relationship they establish strong relationships with their guests and take risks to improve their guests experiences integrated marketing communication campaign on aramarkcom s front page there are several pictures with text and awards they have won for example fortune worlds admired companies  best employers  and  worlds most ethical companies which showed that aramark is a highly responsible company mass communications advertising sales promotion and public relations types of mass communication activitiessales promotion  low degree  high degree online couponsdegree  advertising ads on youtube and commercialsdegree  public relations building communities support neighborhooddegree  media options for aramarkscale is   low importance  high importance newspaper television radio magazines outdoor ads internet social media mobile personal selling personal selling aramark is using both direct sales and missionary salesdirect sales aramark has some salespeople who introduce their services or uniforms to its customers directlymissionary sales our customers may recommend aramark to other companies schools or hospitalstype of salespeople aramark is involved withinside sales support phone calls to make sales and help customersfield salesperson  providing food servicetechnical salesperson  equipment maintenanceservice salesperson people who sell intangible products like cleaning servicesroles and responsibilities of salespeopleall group members tried to call email aramark but sadly no one replied back or could direct us to people that could answer the types of questions we wanted answered pricing objectives and strategies pricing sensitivity aramarks products have a medium  price sensitivity their goods are price sensitive but they also have services services arent as price sensitive because the customer will be willing to pay more to make sure the job gets done right once they purchase the service they cant give it back pricing strategies valuebased and costbasedaramark uses costbased pricing so they can meet the demands of their suppliers namely boars head food products if they increase their prices nationally aramark has to comply however aramark does try to use valuebased pricing as well to meet customer demands understanding the customer in the food service industry is crucialcustomer value proposition operational excellence from the big three sodexo compass group and aramark aramark is the smallest company so they dont strive for product leadership it is also difficult to strive for customer intimacy when you operate on a global scale aramark strives for operational excellence so they can give their customers what they want at the lowest possible price they translate their clients needs and expectations into consistently superior results aramark builds and benefits from brand equity by making sure the customers are fully aware of the products they sell awareness this leads to the customers being satisfied and becoming more loyal and returning loyalty due to the bulk in quality of the products customers receive large amounts of products for a low price all of these aspects allow aramark to be very successful and benefit them over competitors aramarks dominate planninginnovation strategy is market development they provide goods and services in nearly every industry and they continue to try to provide services in even more marketsintroduction phasearamark healthcare technologiesenergy managementgrowth phase food service and refreshmentsclinical technology and services maturity phase uniforms and work apparelfacilities managementdecline phase college catering product life cycle curve low degree  high 